I think for vidya it is very important to have some RNG/randomness - some space for the divine. This way there is always a chance for a Deus ex machina - when League had old runes back in the day one time I played top against a Graves with 1% crit rune. Buddy came to gank me...

And he somehow landed crit on both of us and got 2 kills. I wad not mad, I knew the Heavens simply had decided to give him the victory that day. This is also why I loved TF2 crits and Counter Strike spraying with weapons. RNGesus IS Jesus. Randomness makes for a good game.
